'''''The Divine Spark''''' is a 1935 [[Cinema of the United Kingdom|British]] [[musical film]] directed by [[Carmine Gallone]] and starring [[Marta Eggerth]], [[Phillip Holmes]], [[Benita Hume]] and [[Donald Calthrop]].<ref>[http://ftvdb.bfi.org.uk/sift/title/163220 BFI Database]</ref> An [[Italian-language]] version ''[[Casta Diva]]'' was shot simultaneously.

==Cast==
* [[Marta Eggerth]] - Maddalena Fumaroli
* [[Phillip Holmes]] - [[Vincenzo Bellini]]
* [[Benita Hume]] - [[Giuditta Pasta]]
* [[Donald Calthrop]] - Judge Fumaroli
* [[Arthur Margetson]] - Ernesto Tosi
* [[Edmund Breon]] - [[Gioacchino Rossini]]
* [[Basil Gill]] - Romanie
* [[Hugh Miller (actor)|Hugh Miller]] - [[Niccolo Paganini]]
* [[Edward Chapman (actor)|Edward Chapman]] - [[Saverio Mercadante]]
* [[John Clements]] - Fiorino
* [[John Deverell]] - King
* [[Felix Aylmer]] - Butler
* [[Peter Gawthorne]] - [[Felice Romani]]

